sync.name: sync

revisions.description: MIB version 01.00.01 Added esmcTable. Changed MAX-ACCESS clause from read-write to read-create in tables with row status. Changed STATUS clause of timingSinkEthPortRole from current to deprecated
Improved description of syncMibVersion Removed TimeTicks from IMPORTS list

syncMibVersion.name: syncMibVersion
syncMibVersion.description: Numerical version of this module. The string version of this MIB have the following format: XX.YY.ZZ so, for example, the value 1 should be interpreted as 00.00.01 and the value 10001 should be interpreted as 01.00.01.

timingGeneratorId.name: timingGeneratorId
timingGeneratorId.description: This object is used as Index of the Timing Generator Table.

timingGeneratorT4vsT0.name: timingGeneratorT4vsT0
timingGeneratorT4vsT0.description: This object is used to set or reset the condition T4 equal T0.

timingGeneratorWtrTime.name: timingGeneratorWtrTime
timingGeneratorWtrTime.description: Wait Time to Restore in minutes (0..12).

timingGeneratorSinkLosSet.name: timingGeneratorSinkLosSet
timingGeneratorSinkLosSet.description: Wait time (seconds) before to set Los of reference signal.

timingGeneratorSinkLosReset.name: timingGeneratorSinkLosReset
timingGeneratorSinkLosReset.description: Wait time (seconds) before to reset Los of reference signal.

timingGeneratorT0SquelchAlarm.name: timingGeneratorT0SquelchAlarm
timingGeneratorT0SquelchAlarm.description: T0 squelch Alarm (Probable cause = xxx) with associated severity.

timingGeneratorT4SquelchAlarm.name: timingGeneratorT4SquelchAlarm
timingGeneratorT4SquelchAlarm.description: T4 squelch Alarm (Probable cause = xxx) with associated severity.

timingGeneratorFreeRunningStatus.name: timingGeneratorFreeRunningStatus
timingGeneratorFreeRunningStatus.description: Free running status (Probable cause = xxx) with associated severity.

timingGeneratorHoldoverStatus.name: timingGeneratorHoldoverStatus
timingGeneratorHoldoverStatus.description: Holdover status (Probable cause = xxx) with associated severity.

timingGeneratorActiveStatus.name: timingGeneratorActiveStatus
timingGeneratorActiveStatus.description: Active status (Probable cause = xxx) with associated severity.

timingGeneratorT4MinimumQuality.name: timingGeneratorT4MinimumQuality
timingGeneratorT4MinimumQuality.description: If the Quality Level of the signal used to derive T4 falls below timingGeneratorT4MinimumQuality then the output will be squelched. The value ql-DNU inhibits T4 squelch due to this minimum Quality Level. This feature is enabled by timingGeneratorT4Squelch when timingGeneratorQualityEnable is on(2).

timingGeneratorT0PreferredSource.name: timingGeneratorT0PreferredSource
timingGeneratorT0PreferredSource.description: Object identifier of the leaf timingSinkGenId of the timingSink instance selected as preferential clock source of T0. If no preferential timing sink is selected, the value should be set to the OBJECT IDENTIFIER { 0 0 }.

timingGeneratorT4PreferredSource.name: timingGeneratorT4PreferredSource
timingGeneratorT4PreferredSource.description: Object identifier of the leaf timingSinkGenId of the timingSink instance selected as preferential clock source of T4. If no preferential timing sink is selected, the value should be set to the OBJECT IDENTIFIER { 0 0 }.

timingGeneratorRowStatus.name: timingGeneratorRowStatus
timingGeneratorRowStatus.description: Status of this row of timingGeneratorTable.

timingGeneratorT4Squelch.name: timingGeneratorT4Squelch
timingGeneratorT4Squelch.description: This object is used to enable/disable T4 squelch.

timingGeneratorStatusControl.name: timingGeneratorStatusControl
timingGeneratorStatusControl.description: Clock generator operating mode control. This item is linked to a manual operation (ManOpRecord) instance.

timingGeneratorT0ForcedSource.name: timingGeneratorT0ForcedSource
timingGeneratorT0ForcedSource.description: Object identifier of the leaf timingSinkGenId of the timingSink instance selected as forced clock source of T0. If no forced timing sink is selected, the value should be set to the OBJECT IDENTIFIER { 0 0 }.

timingGeneratorT4ForcedSource.name: timingGeneratorT4ForcedSource
timingGeneratorT4ForcedSource.description: Object identifier of the leaf timingSinkGenId of the timingSink instance selected as forced clock source of T4. If no forced timing sink is selected, the value should be set to the OBJECT IDENTIFIER { 0 0 }.

timingGeneratorWtrClearSource.name: timingGeneratorWtrClearSource
timingGeneratorWtrClearSource.description: Object identifier of the leaf timingSinkGenId of the timingSink instance selected to clear WTR time. On read, this object return alvays an OBJECT IDENTIFIER {0 0}.

timingSinkGenId.name: timingSinkGenId
timingSinkGenId.description: This object is used as Index of the timingGeneratorTable and defines in union with timingSinkType and timingSinkId the reference signal.

timingSinkId.name: timingSinkId
timingSinkId.description: This object is used as Index of the timingSinkTable and defines in union with timingSinkType and timingSinkGenId the reference signal.

timingSinkType.name: timingSinkType
timingSinkType.description: This object is used as Index of the timingSinkTable and defines if the reference signal is used to generate T0 or T4 system clock.

timingSinkIfIndex.name: timingSinkIfIndex
timingSinkIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value the agent selected for this timingSink interface.

timingSinkSelector.name: timingSinkSelector
timingSinkSelector.description: This object is used to select one of the possible clock source connected to this timingSink. Valid values are listed in timingSinkSelectorTable: only values of timingSinkSelectorId related to this instance of timinkSinkRecord are accepted. Only the values corresponding to the index timingSinkSelectorId of timinkSinkSelectorTable related to this instance of timinkSinkRecord will be accepted.

timingSinkPriority.name: timingSinkPriority
timingSinkPriority.description: This object is used to set the priority of the reference signal (p1 is the highest priority).

timingSinkLabel.name: timingSinkLabel
timingSinkLabel.description: ASCII string used to describe the reference signal when a trap is sent.

timingSinkLosAlarm.name: timingSinkLosAlarm
timingSinkLosAlarm.description: Loss of reference signal (Probable cause = xxx) alarm with associated severity.

timingSinkDriftAlarm.name: timingSinkDriftAlarm
timingSinkDriftAlarm.description: Drift of reference signal (Probable cause = xxx) alarm with associated severity.

timingSinkActiveStatus.name: timingSinkActiveStatus
timingSinkActiveStatus.description: Active status (Probable cause = xxx) status for the reference signal.

timingSinkSentQuality.name: timingSinkSentQuality
timingSinkSentQuality.description: Quality level written in the S1 byte of the outgoing STM-n.

timingSinkE1Sabit.name: timingSinkE1Sabit
timingSinkE1Sabit.description: Specifies the San synchronization status bit used to indicate the clock quality level. Meaningful when the Sink source is an E1

timingSinkEthPortRole.name: timingSinkEthPortRole
timingSinkEthPortRole.description: This item configures how to handle the role of a 1000BASE-T port when it is used as a source of timing: choosing 'static', the role is set according ethLanPhyTable settings, choosing 'dynamic', the role is set consistently with the timing direction over the 1000baseT link chosen by SSM protocol.

timingSinkRowStatus.name: timingSinkRowStatus
timingSinkRowStatus.description: Status of this row of timingSinkTable

timingGeneratorManualSwitch.name: timingGeneratorManualSwitch
timingGeneratorManualSwitch.description: timingGeneratorId of the forced timingGenerator instance. If no preferred timing generator is selected, the value should be set to 0.

timingGeneratorForcedSwitch.name: timingGeneratorForcedSwitch
timingGeneratorForcedSwitch.description: timingGeneratorId of the forced timingGenerator instance. If no forced timing generator is selected, the value should be set to 0.

timingGeneratorT0SquelchAlarmSeverityCod.name: timingGeneratorT0SquelchAlarmSeverityCode
timingGeneratorT0SquelchAlarmSeverityCod.description: Defines the severity associated to the TimingGeneratorT0SquelchAlarm and enables/disables the trap generation on status change event.

timingGeneratorT4SquelchAlarmSeverityCod.name: timingGeneratorT4SquelchAlarmSeverityCode
timingGeneratorT4SquelchAlarmSeverityCod.description: Defines the severity associated to the timingGeneratorT4SquelchAlarm and enables/disables the trap generation on status change event.

timingGeneratorFreeRunningStatusSeverity.name: timingGeneratorFreeRunningStatusSeverityCode
timingGeneratorFreeRunningStatusSeverity.description: Defines the severity associated to the timingGeneratorFreeRunningStatus and enables/disables the trap generation on status change event.

timingGeneratorHoldoverStatusSeverityCod.name: timingGeneratorHoldoverStatusSeverityCode
timingGeneratorHoldoverStatusSeverityCod.description: Defines the severity associated to the timingGeneratorHoldoverStatus and enables/disables the trap generation on status change event.

timingGeneratorActiveStatusSeverityCode.name: timingGeneratorActiveStatusSeverityCode
timingGeneratorActiveStatusSeverityCode.description: Defines the severity associated to the timingGeneratorActiveStatus and enables/disables the trap generation on status change event.

timingSinkLosAlarmSeverityCode.name: timingSinkLosAlarmSeverityCode
timingSinkLosAlarmSeverityCode.description: Defines the severity associated to the TimingSinkLosAlarm and enables/disables the trap generation on status change event.

timingSinkDriftAlarmSeverityCode.name: timingSinkDriftAlarmSeverityCode
timingSinkDriftAlarmSeverityCode.description: Defines the severity associated to the TimingSinkDriftAlarm and enables/disables the trap generation on status change event.

timingSinkActiveStatusSeverityCode.name: timingSinkActiveStatusSeverityCode
timingSinkActiveStatusSeverityCode.description: Defines the severity associated to the timingSinkActiveStatus and enables/disables the trap generation on status change event.

timingSinkSelectorRecord.name: timingSinkSelectorRecord
timingSinkSelectorRecord.description: TimingSinkSelector entry. Several instances of this entry can be create for each instance of timingSinkTable. Each entry represents a possible source selected by a multiplexer outside the SETS for a specific timingSink. Only the values corresponding to the index timingSinkSelectorId can be set to timingSinkSelector.

timingSinkSelectorId.name: timingSinkSelectorId
timingSinkSelectorId.description: This object is used as Index of the timingSinkSelectorTable and defines in union with timingSinkGenId, timingSinkType and timingSinkId the selected source by a multiplexer outside the SETS.

timingSinkSelectorLabel.name: timingSinkSelectorLabel
timingSinkSelectorLabel.description: ASCII string used to describe the selectable timing source.

esmcRecord.name: esmcRecord
esmcRecord.description: esmcTable entry. Every entries describes an ESMC channel of a TE interface.

esmcSsmEnable.name: esmcSsmEnable
esmcSsmEnable.description: This object enables SSM messaging on this ifIndex.

esmcQlRx.name: esmcQlRx
esmcQlRx.description: This object show quality received on ESMC-PDU this interface.

esmcQlTx.name: esmcQlTx
esmcQlTx.description: This object show quality transmitted in ESMC-PDU on this interface.

esmcPktsRx.name: esmcPktsRx
esmcPktsRx.description: This object contains the total number of received ESMC-PDU packets on this interface.

esmcPktsTx.name: esmcPktsTx
esmcPktsTx.description: This object contains the total number of transmitted ESMC-PDU packets on this interface.

esmcPktsRxDropped.name: esmcPktsRxDropped
esmcPktsRxDropped.description: This object contains the total number of dropped ESMC-PDU packets on this interface.

esmcPktsRxErrored.name: esmcPktsRxErrored
esmcPktsRxErrored.description: This object contains the total number of dropped ESMC-PDU packets whose processing(decoding) resulted into error.

esmc1000BaseTRole.name: esmc1000BaseTRole
esmc1000BaseTRole.description: This object allows to input the clock generator role of a 1000BaseT interface. This objects is applicable when the quality management is disabled (timingGeneratorQualityEnable set to off(1)) and to all interfaces not connected to any timingSink when the quality management is enabled.

esmcRowStatus.name: esmcRowStatus
esmcRowStatus.description: Status of this row of esmcTable.
